Lateral Damage<br />
<br />
I&#39;m giving my decklist for Watto to demonstrate the idea behind BSG.  This deck represents the best possible deck I have found to showcase what Biker Scout Gear will do to the game.  I imagined BSG helping Scum & Villainy, BHBM, Invasion, Endor Ops, and maybe even Ralltir Ops.  But there was really no way to separate these decks from Hunt Down, Dark Deal, the Maul deck, or Watto.  A lot of decks would see a benefit to having protection from the Epp deploy and die strategy.  I chose Watto because it is a deck that immediately sees the benefit of being able to keep Watto alive and not having to worry about losing 5 to 10 force on the first turn.  <br />
<br />
This is an annoying deck that I would never intentionally make a helper card for.  There are several interesting things to notice in this deck.  First, I included Epps.  This isn&#39;t by accident but instead was meant to prove a point.  There is nothing in BSG that makes Epps worthless to play with.  They are still great utility characters.  They defend a site well and that is why they are included in the deck.  <br />
<br />
